## Context
isViewportOnly is calculated fresh on every renderTiles() with no hysteresis.
Mode can flip between frames if user pans while zooming.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/pdf-page-element.ts`

## Current Behavior (Lines 723-725)
```typescript
const isViewportOnly = minTileX > 0 || minTileY > 0 ||
  (maxTileX + 1) * pdfTileSize < pdfWidth - pdfTileSize ||
  (maxTileY + 1) * pdfTileSize < pdfHeight - pdfTileSize;
```

## Problem
- Frame 1: Full coverage → isViewportOnly=false → full-page CSS
- Frame 2: Slight pan → isViewportOnly=true → viewport-only CSS
- Visual jump from CSS size/transform change

## Fix
Add hysteresis or gesture-awareness:
```typescript
// Lock mode during active gesture
if (this.isGestureActive && this.lockedMode !== null) {
  isViewportOnly = this.lockedMode === 'viewport-only';
} else {
  isViewportOnly = /* calculation */;
  if (!this.isGestureActive) {
    this.lockedMode = isViewportOnly ? 'viewport-only' : 'full-page';
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Mode does NOT switch during active zoom/pan gesture
- [ ] Mode switch only occurs after gesture settles
- [ ] Hysteresis prevents oscillation at threshold

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] No visual jumps when panning at mode boundary
- [ ] Mode transitions smooth after gesture ends

## Context
Council mandated: Soft constraints during gesture, hard constraints at gesture end.
ZoomStateManager needs to support both constraint modes.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/zoom-state-manager.ts`

## Implementation
```typescript
interface ZoomStateConfig {
  // ... existing fields
  softConstraintFactor: number;  // 0.3 = 30% rubber-band resistance
}

// Add to ZoomStateManager class
constrainCamera(isGestureActive: boolean): Camera {
  if (isGestureActive) {
    return this.applySoftConstraints();
  }
  return this.applyHardConstraints();
}

private applySoftConstraints(): Camera {
  const { x, y, zoom } = this.state;
  const { minX, maxX, minY, maxY } = this.calculateBounds(zoom);

  let targetX = x, targetY = y;
  const factor = this.config.softConstraintFactor;

  if (x < minX) targetX = minX + (x - minX) * factor; // Rubber-band
  if (x > maxX) targetX = maxX + (x - maxX) * factor;
  if (y < minY) targetY = minY + (y - minY) * factor;
  if (y > maxY) targetY = maxY + (y - maxY) * factor;

  return { x: targetX, y: targetY, z: zoom };
}

private applyHardConstraints(): Camera {
  const { x, y, zoom } = this.state;
  const { minX, maxX, minY, maxY } = this.calculateBounds(zoom);

  return {
    x: Math.max(minX, Math.min(maxX, x)),
    y: Math.max(minY, Math.min(maxY, y)),
    z: zoom
  };
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `constrainCamera(isGestureActive)` routes to correct constraint mode
- [ ] Soft constraints allow rubber-band effect (30% resistance)
- [ ] Hard constraints clamp to exact bounds
- [ ] Bounds calculation respects current zoom level

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] Rubber-band effect visible when panning past edges during gesture
- [ ] Camera snaps to bounds after gesture ends

## Problem
At 16x zoom threshold, coordinate system changes (full-page → viewport-only) but tiles aren't invalidated.

## Solution
Clear cached tiles and abort in-flight requests when crossing the threshold:

```typescript
if (isHighZoom && !wasHighZoom) {
  for (const page of visiblePages) {
    getTileCacheManager().evictByPage(page);
    this.pageElements.get(page)?.clearCanvas();
  }
  this.renderCoordinator?.abortAllPending();
}
```

## Location
