## Overview
Service to fetch metadata (title, description, image) from external URLs for preview display.

## Requirements
- Fetch OpenGraph/Twitter Card metadata
- Fallback to HTML title tag
- Cache results to avoid repeated fetches
- Handle CORS limitations gracefully
- Timeout handling for slow sites

## Implementation

### MetadataService
```typescript
interface UrlMetadata {
  url: string;
  title?: string;
  description?: string;
  image?: string;
  siteName?: string;
  favicon?: string;
  fetchedAt: number;
}

class UrlMetadataService {
  private cache: Map<string, UrlMetadata>;
  private fetchTimeout: number = 5000;

  async fetchMetadata(url: string): Promise<UrlMetadata>;
  clearCache(): void;
}
```

### Fetching Strategy
1. **Primary**: Use Obsidian's `requestUrl` (handles CORS)
2. **Parse**: Extract meta tags from HTML
3. **Fallback**: Just show URL + domain

### Meta Tag Extraction
```typescript
function extractMetadata(html: string, url: string): UrlMetadata {
  const parser = new DOMParser();
  const doc = parser.parseFromString(html, 'text/html');

  const getMeta = (name: string) => 
    doc.querySelector(`meta[property="${name}"], meta[name="${name}"]`)
      ?.getAttribute('content');

  return {
    url,
    title: getMeta('og:title') || doc.title,
    description: getMeta('og:description') || getMeta('description'),
    image: getMeta('og:image'),
    siteName: getMeta('og:site_name') || new URL(url).hostname,
    favicon: `${new URL(url).origin}/favicon.ico`,
    fetchedAt: Date.now(),
  };
}
```

### Caching
- In-memory cache with 1-hour TTL
- Optional persistence to IndexedDB

