## Overview
Core infrastructure for managing nested/recursive popups. This is the foundation for the entire rabbit hole feature.

## Requirements
- Popup stack/tree data structure tracking active popups
- Each popup knows its parent and children
- Position calculation with cascade offset (each level offset 20-30px down-right)
- Global event coordination (click-away closes deepest popup first)
- Max viewport bounds enforcement
- Animation for open/close transitions

## Implementation

### PopupManager Class
```typescript
interface PopupInstance {
  id: string;
  parentId: string | null;
  position: { x: number; y: number };
  depth: number;
  content: PopupContent;
  element: HTMLElement | null;
}

class RecursivePopupManager {
  private stack: Map<string, PopupInstance>;
  private activeRoot: string | null;

  open(content: PopupContent, parentId?: string, triggerRect?: DOMRect): string;
  close(id: string): void;
  closeAll(): void;
  getDepth(id: string): number;
  calculatePosition(parentRect: DOMRect, depth: number): Position;
}
```

### Position Cascade Algorithm
1. Start from trigger element rect
2. Add offset based on depth: `x + (depth * 25), y + (depth * 20)`
3. Clamp to viewport bounds
4. If would overflow, try opposite side
5. If still overflow, reduce offset

### Event Handling
- Click outside any popup: close all
- Click outside deepest popup but inside parent: close only deepest
- Escape key: close deepest popup
- Hover timeout: optional auto-close after delay

