## Problem
Epoch validation was removed from `renderTiles()` to prevent high-res tile starvation, but this allows stale tiles from different viewports to be drawn.

## Solution
Restore epoch validation with a wider tolerance (10 epochs instead of 0):

```typescript
const EPOCH_TOLERANCE = 10;
if (currentEpoch !== undefined && tiles.some(t => t.scaleEpoch !== undefined)) {
  tiles = tiles.filter(t => {
    if (t.scaleEpoch === undefined) return true;
    return Math.abs(currentEpoch - t.scaleEpoch) <= EPOCH_TOLERANCE;
  });
}
```

