## Objective

Implement a 3-tier caching system for EPUB, mirroring the PDF tile cache architecture, with memory pressure awareness and smart eviction.

## Background

The PDF renderer uses a sophisticated 3-tier cache:
- **L1**: ImageBitmaps (GPU-ready, fast display)
- **L2**: Blobs (quick decode, larger capacity)
- **L3**: Metadata (never evicted)

EPUB currently uses simple Map caches with fixed TTL, no tier awareness, and no memory pressure handling.

## PDF Cache Architecture (Reference)

| Tier | PDF Content | Capacity | Eviction |
|------|-------------|----------|----------|
| L1 | ImageBitmap | ~50 tiles | LRU, focal-point aware |
| L2 | Blob | ~200 tiles | LRU, persistent option |
| L3 | Metadata, text | Unlimited | Never evicted |

**Key File:** `src/reader/renderer/pdf/tile-cache-manager.ts`
- Lines 5-30: Cache tier documentation
- Lines 556-604: Configuration and JPEG cache
- Lines 1748-1860: Memory pressure handling
- Lines 2799-2810: Focal-point-aware eviction

## Proposed EPUB Cache Architecture

| Tier | Content | Capacity | Eviction |
|------|---------|----------|----------|
| L1 | DOM elements (visible chapters) | 3-5 chapters | Visibility-based |
| L2 | Parsed HTML strings | 10-20 chapters | LRU by access time |
| L3 | Spine structure, raw ZIP data | Full book | Never evicted |

### L1: DOM Tier (Hot)
- **Content**: Fully rendered DOM elements attached to navigator
- **Size**: 3-5 chapters (current sliding window)
- **Eviction**: When chapter scrolls out of visibility + buffer
- **Cost**: High memory (full DOM tree), instant display

### L2: Parsed HTML Tier (Warm)
- **Content**: Parsed HTML strings ready for DOM insertion
- **Size**: 10-20 chapters based on device tier
- **Eviction**: LRU with access time tracking
- **Cost**: Medium memory (string), fast DOM creation (~10-50ms)

### L3: Raw Data Tier (Cold)
- **Content**: EPUB spine, ZIP file references, chapter metadata
- **Size**: Full book (relatively small)
- **Eviction**: Never (required for navigation)
- **Cost**: Low memory, requires parsing (~50-200ms)

## Current EPUB Caching

