pdf-page-element.ts:renderTiles() - near line 1000

**Priority:** P4 (Medium)
**Council Consensus:** Do not swap rendering modes (Full Page ↔ Tiled) during a pinch.

## Problem
Mode transition check happens AFTER camera moves:
```typescript
// 1. zoomCameraToPoint() → camera moves
// 2. constraint applied
// 3. MODE CHECK → detects transition
// 4. prepareForFullPageRender() → canvas.opacity='0' (BLANK!)
```

This causes:
1. Snapshot captures wrong position (camera already moved)
2. Blank flash during mode transition
3. Visual jump when entering/exiting tiled mode

## Implementation
1. **Detect transition BEFORE camera moves:** Check if zoom will cross threshold
2. **Capture snapshot at current position:** Before any state changes
3. **Defer actual mode switch:** Keep current mode during gesture
4. **Pre-render in background:** Start preparing tiles for target mode
5. **Execute transition on gesture end:** Swap seamlessly when content ready

```typescript
handleZoomChange(newZoom: number, isGestureActive: boolean) {
  const shouldBeTiled = newZoom >= this.TILING_THRESHOLD;

  if (isGestureActive) {
    // Note pending transition, don't execute yet
    this.pendingMode = shouldBeTiled ? 'tiled' : 'full-page';
    // Pre-render in background
    this.preRenderForMode(this.pendingMode, newZoom);
  } else {
    // Gesture ended, execute transition
    if (this.pendingMode !== this.currentMode) {
      this.executeTransition(this.pendingMode);
    }
  }
}
```

